gw.api.web.accounting

Class UIWriteOffCreation

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.web.accounting.UIWriteOffCreation

  • public class UIWriteOffCreation
extends java.lang.Object
    Decorator for write-offs (positive) and negative write-offs in the UI. This should always be used to setup write-offs in the UI before execution (with approval handling)

      • doWriteOff

        public void doWriteOff()
        Executes the write-off wrapped by this class using the approval framework. Will result in an approval activity if the current user does not have authority to execute this write-off

      • setAmount

        public void setAmount(MonetaryAmount value)
        Setting amount is disallowed directly on the write-off, because you should not be changing the write-off amount after the write-off has been executed.
        Parameters:
        value - The amount to write-off
